## 4. Styling — Non-Negotiable Rules

### No hardcoded values. Ever.
NEVER use hex, rgb(), hsl(), or any literal color value in JSX,
inline styles, or className strings.

❌ Wrong:
<div style={{ color: '#5c7cfa' }}>
<div className="text-[#5c7cfa]">
<div style={{ background: 'hsl(228, 94%, 67%)' }}>

✅ Correct:
<div className="text-primary">
<div className="bg-accent">

### No token passing as props or inline styles
NEVER pass design tokens as inline style props between components.
Tokens are consumed via Tailwind classes or global CSS only.

❌ Wrong:
<Component color="var(--primary)" />
<div style={{ color: 'var(--primary)' }}>

✅ Correct:
<div className="text-primary">

### Tailwind classes must map to globals.css tokens
Only use Tailwind classes that correspond to CSS variables defined in
globals.css — e.g. bg-background, text-foreground, border-border,
text-muted-foreground, bg-card, text-primary, bg-destructive.

For any style not covered by an existing token, add a class to
globals.css and use that. Never use arbitrary Tailwind values.

❌ Wrong:
<div className="text-[#333] bg-[rgba(0,0,0,0.4)]">

✅ Correct: add to globals.css, then:
<div className="my-new-class">

### Always use cn() for className composition
Import cn from @/utils/cn. Never manually concatenate className strings.

❌ Wrong:
className={'base-class ' + (isActive ? 'active' : '')}

✅ Correct:
className={cn('base-class', isActive && 'active')}